defaultA respondent 
defaultin
default Buckinghamshire said: “Some of my GPs are often biased by the diagnosis of M.E. when I try and discuss another issue or want to seek further advice or tests. It can also take some time to discuss a condition properly in light of other conditions I have, which can be difficult in a 10 minute slot.”
default&#xa0;
default2.5
default. Action for M.E. supports the view that 
defaulta holistic approach, encouraging patients to discuss more than one symptom and condition, in each appointment, would be helpful. We appreciate that GPs must operate within strict time constraints, so it would be helpful if patients with M.E. and other long-term conditions could be encouraged to book double appointments.
