default3.14
default.
default A majority of people with M.E. (86% - see paragraph 3.6) told us they have been offered no social care services in the last year. Given the disabling physical symptoms of M.E., and the fact that 25% of patient
defaults are severely affected (house- 
defaultor bed-bound), 
defaultwe believe it is important to have a 
defaultnational approach to improving quality and developing 
defaultsocial care
default, with specific guidance for specialist conditions such as M.E.
