default Some examples of effective patient contribution to better outcomes include:
default&#xa0;
default5.6
default.
default A respondent in Kent said: “The fluctuations and limitations of my illness (dysphonia/sensory sensitivity) make consultations either difficult to attend or very long (always double appointments). So about a year ago my GP provided me with his surgery email address so that I can provide him with updates and relevant research material prior to consultati
defaulton to inform my on-going care. 
defaultAs a result his knowledge of my illness and support for me has increased and my consultations with him are more constructive.”
default&#xa0;
default5.7
default.
default 
defaultListening to patients 
defaultas individuals
default, as well as through national bodies such as Healthwatch England, is
default key to better patient outcomes.
default Action for M.E. is encouraged to see that more than a third of patients have had this experience – but they are still in the minority. 
defaultA fundamental shift in attitude is required.
